-- Peru Stocks: Alturas, Ferreyros, Intergroup, Panoro Minerals
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-01T21:32:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/peru-stocks-alturas-ferreyros-intergroup-panoro-minerals.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 1.1 percent to 22,982.85. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  gained 1.3 percent to 2,895.84.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 9.1 percent to 12 cents after copper
advanced to the highest since Feb. 9.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., jumped 5.6 percent to 2.99 soles after U.S.
stocks advanced, said BBVA Continental SAB’s Chief Executive
Officer Jorge Ramos.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, gained for a fifth session, adding 5.3
percent to 80 cents, a five-year high. Gold futures rebounded
from yesterday’s decline.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of
Peru’s fourth-largest bank Interbank, rose 5.1 percent to $31
after the central bank said bank lending increased 19 percent in
January.  To contact the reporter on this story:
